Aspect	Production	Manufacturing
Definition	The process of creating goods or services.	The process of converting raw materials into finished goods.
Scope	Broader, includes services and intangible products.	Narrower, focused on physical goods.
Processes	Can involve various methods, including assembly, processing, and service delivery.	Primarily involves mechanical and chemical processes.
Output	Can be goods, services, or a combination of both.	Primarily tangible products.
Examples	Film production, software development, and agriculture.	Automobile manufacturing, electronics assembly, and textile production.
Flexibility	Often more adaptable to changes in demand and trends.	Typically less flexible due to fixed processes and equipment.
Labor	May involve skilled labor, creative professionals, and service workers.	Often involves skilled labor, technicians, and assembly line workers.
